If length are not same return false.
otherwise
There are 3 possible cases for each chars at same index
1. if s[i] == t[i] then continue;
2. else find difference (if -ve add 26) which will be in range [0,25], for this we take 26 size array **step** to remember the which moves we have already taken, and update **step** for next possible move we can take.
**example:**
diff = t[i]-s[i];
For diff = 1, possible moves are 1, 27, 53 ...
For diff = 2, possible moves are 2, 28, 54 ...
For diff = 3, possible moves are 3, 29, 55 ... 
.
.
.
For diff = 25, possible moves are 25, 51, 77 ... 

3. Whenever we found the move we need for this is greater K return false. 

