solutions.content:
**Intution :**

For such kind of balancing parenthesis first thing should strike is Greedy along with Stack to balance. 
Lets see how to solve these kind of problems.

* Idea is simple, at every index in string we need to keep the balance of opening and closing brackets i.e.

	count of '(' >= count of ')'  -> for all index i from 0 to n

* And to track balance at *every index i* we have two conditions : 

	1. if element at current index i is '(' 
		-> do balance + 2 , since for two ') )' we have one '(' 

	2. else if element is ')', then do [balance - 2]
		 -> if next is also ')' then increment i as we got two consecutive '))'
		 -> else we need to insert one ')' next to this. So increment number of insertions counter.

* Also, if at any point this inequality fails i.e. 
	* balance become negative or 

		*		count of '(' < count of ')'

	* We need to balance that by inserting (actually increamenting count) counter bracket .

			if balance < 0, we have two cases either balance = -1 or -2

				-> When balance = -1, this means we have only '('
					and we need to insert one '(' and one ')'.
					So incease the counter of number of insertions by 2.

				-> When balance = -2, this means we have two consecutive ')' i.e ') ) '
					 and we just need single '(' to balance it.
					 Thus increase counter only by 1. 

				In the end, we also need to reset balance to 0 as we have '( ) )' -> valid string

* Now, there may be some case when balance > 0. This means we have some extra '(' which do not have their counter parts. 
* So, we have to insert those many ')' to make balance=0. Thus, increament remaining to counter.


# Code : 	

```
int minInsertions(string s) {

	int n = s.size();
	int cntInsertions = 0, balance = 0;

	for(int i=0; i<n; )
	{
	if(s[i] == '(') balance += 2;
	else if(s[i] == ')')
	{
		balance -= 2;
		if(i+1<n && s[i+1] == ')')
		{
			i++;
		}
		else 
		{
			cntInsertions++;
		}
	}
	if(balance < 0)
	{
		if(balance == -2) cntInsertions++;
		else cntInsertions += 2;
		balance = 0;
	}
	i++;

	// cout << balance << " " << cntInsertions << endl;
	}
	cntInsertions += balance;
	return cntInsertions;
}
```

**Time : O(N) Single pass**
**Space : O(1)**

