# Intuition - Idea is every ')' should be enclosed by '(' and ')'
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach - 
    1. Use a stack to store every '('
    2. On ')', initially consider no '(' and ')' enclosing it, hence ops = 2, if there is '(' on top of stack, ops = 1 and also if there is ')' after current char, ops = 0.
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minInsertions(string s) {
        stack<char> st;
        int ans = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < s.size(); i++) {
            if(s[i] == '(') {
                st.push(s[i]);
            } else {
                // initially consider no '(' and ')' enclosing a ')', ops = 2
                int currInc = 2;
                if(i+1 < s.size() && s[i+1] == ')') {
                    currInc--;
                    i++;
                }
                if(st.size() > 0 && st.top() == '(') {
                    st.pop(); currInc--;
                }
                ans += currInc;
            }
        }

        return ans + 2 * st.size();
    }
};
```

