if looked carefully, this question reduces to the problem which is a slight variation of the problem
https://leetcode.com/problems/number-of-wonderful-substrings/

if we want to make a substing palindrome, it either could have even length or odd length, for even length palindrome, we need all the constituting characters to occur even number of times, 
and to have a palindrome of odd length, we need all the other characters to occur even number of times except that one character at the middle which will occur once. 

So, at last the problem reduces to finding the length of longest substring that has at most 1 character that occurs odd number of times.

here is the solution, we will be storing the first index of every prefix xor.

class Solution {
public:

    int longestAwesome(string s) {

        // i think the question reduces to finding the longest substring having at at most one character that occurs odd number of times

        int mask=0;
        unordered_map<int,int> m;

        m[0]=-1; // prefix xor and its index
        int ans=INT_MIN;

        for(int i=0;i<s.size();i++)
        {
            mask^= (1<<(s[i]-'0'));

            if(m.count(mask^0))
                ans= max(ans,i-m[mask^0]);

            for(int k=0;k<32;k++)
            {
                int copy= mask;

                copy^=(1<<k);

                if(m.count(copy))
                    ans= max(ans,i-m[copy]);
            }
            if(m.count(mask)==0)
                m[mask]=i;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

