# Approach
1) We know that 'a' - 'A' = 32, and is same for every alphabatic character
2) To make the string good,we have to eliminate adjacent characters that make the string bad.

3) check if top element of stack+32 is equal to strings character at i location or char+32 is equal to top element of stack, in both the cases you have to pop out the element else push following character of string

4) append stack elements in ans string and return the reverse of it.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string makeGood(string str) {
        stack<char>s;
        for(int i=0; i<str.length(); i++){
            if(s.size()==0){
                s.push(str[i]);
                continue;
            }
            if(s.top()+32==str[i] || str[i]+32 == s.top()){
                s.pop();
            }else{
                s.push(str[i]);
            }
        }
        string ans = "";
        while(s.size()){
            ans+=s.top();
            s.pop();
        }
        reverse(ans.begin(),ans.end());
        return ans;
    }
};
```

