# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Create a stack and traverse over the string: 
1. If the stack is empty then push the character in the stack. 
2. If the element at the top of the stack is lowercase letter and next character in the string is same upper case letter or vice-versa then pop that character from the stack. 
3. Otherwise push the character onto the stack.

The characters present in the stack forms the good string.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(N)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string makeGood(string s) {
        stack<char>st;
        for (int i =0  ; i < s.size() ; i++)
        {
            if (st.size() == 0)
            {
                st.push(s[i]);
            }
            else if (st.top() == (s[i]+32) || st.top()+32 == s[i])
            st.pop();
            else
            st.push(s[i]);
        }
        string ans = "";
        while(!st.empty())
        {
            ans.insert(ans.begin(), st.top());
            st.pop();
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

