**If we have k==1 or n==1 we simply return 0.**
If we have **k<=mid** then our answer lies in **(n-1,k)**.
If we have **k==mid+1** then our answer will always be **1**.
If we have **k>mid** the our answer lies in **(n-1,size-k+1)** and we have to  **invert our answer**
