Let f(n,k) be the kth bit of S_{n}. We then have that (assuming valid k): f(1, k) = 0. To compute f(n, k), we count the size of S_{n-1} and determine the whether the appropriate bit lies in S_{n-1}, '1', or reverse(inverse(S_{n-1})), which we can note is equivalent to inverse(reverse(S_{n-1})).

```
public char findKthBit(int n, int k) {
	if (n == 1) return '0';
	int leftHalfSize = ((1 << n) - 1)/2;
	if (k <= leftHalfSize) return findKthBit(n-1, k);
	if (k == leftHalfSize + 1) return '1';
	return findKthBit(n-1, 2*leftHalfSize - k + 2) == '0' ? '1' : '0';
}
```

