solutions.content:
The key idea of this iterative solution is to every time shorten the String Sn, and find the symmetry on the left part if k is bigger than mid point. Using boolean 'toFlip' to record whether or not need to flip after iteration.
```
class Solution {
    public char findKthBit(int n, int k) {

        boolean toFlip=false;
        k--;
        char res = '0';
        int count=1;

        //find the length of Sn stored in 'count'.
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            count = count*2 +1;
        } 

        while(n>1){
            int mid = count/2;

            //if k is exactly the mid point, the temporary result is '1'.
            if(k==mid){
                res = '1';
                break;
            }
            //if k is bigger than mid, which means on the right side if Sn, 
            // we can find the symmetry left part and just flip it.
            else if(k>mid){
                toFlip = !toFlip;
                int diff = k-mid;
                k = mid-diff;
            }
            n--;  
            count /=2;
        }

        if(toFlip){
            if(res=='0'){
                res='1';
            }
            else{
                res='0';
            }
        }

        return res;

    }
}

