solutions.content:
The main idea here is the self-similarity of the string. Because the string of length ```n``` is constructed from the string of length ```n-1``` we can solve this recursively.

In this recursion, the level is always decreased by 1, and no string is actually generated, so the algorithm is O(n) time and O(1) space.
```
class Solution {
public:
    char findKthBit(int n, int k) {
	    // First bit is always 0
        if (k == 1) return '0';

		// The length of the string at level n is 2^n-1, so 2^(n-1) is the halfway index
        int half_len = 1 << (n-1);
		// The halfway index is set to be 1
        if (k == half_len) return '1';

