Idea:
There are two possible origins of a digit, i.e. the initail `0` or `1` that's added during concatenation.
Find out how many time this origin was flipped.
```
char findKthBit(int n, int k) {
    int cnt = 0;
    while (n>0) {
        int pivot = 1 << (n-1);
        if (k == pivot)  // if k equals to 1 << (n-1), it has found the origin
            break;
        if (k > pivot)
            cnt++, k = 2 * pivot - k;  // this is because s was reversed
        n--;
    }
    if (n == 1)
        return cnt % 2 ? '1' : '0';  // if n == 1, it means the origin is 0
    return cnt % 2 ? '0' : '1';  // otherwise, the origin is 1
}
```

