# Approach
Instead of n I use the smallest n value that contains k (log2(k) + 1). The n parameter is ignored. This reduces the number of recursive calls when k is small.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(logk)$$ <= $$O(n)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public char findKthBit(int n, int k) {
        if (k == 1) return '0';
        // reduce n to the smallest n that contains k. log2(k)+1
        int result = findK((int)Math.floor(Math.log(k)/Math.log(2))+1, k);
        return result == 1 ? '1' : '0';
    }

    private int findK(int n, int k) {
        if (n == 1) return 0;

        int mid = 1 << n-1; 
        if (k == mid) return 1;

        if (k < mid) {
            return findK(n-1, k);
        } else {
            return 1 ^ findK(n-1, 2 * mid - k);
        }
    }
}
```

