solutions.content:
We iterate through the array and aompute the prefix sum and calculate which sum we need to have in previous steps.

If we have that sum in past we get its index and compare with previous subarray range that we had (`prev` index). 

In the beggining `prev = -1` which means we do not have any subarray for now, then when we find that subarray we update its value equal to the end index of that range. 

And at each subarray which we found we compare the beggining of new range `index` wih the end index of the last range `prev` and if `index` >= `prev` we increment our answer.
```
class Solution {
    public int maxNonOverlapping(int[] a, int t) {
        int prev = -1;
        Map<Integer,Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        map.put(0,-1);
        int sum = 0;
        int count = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < a.length; i++) {
            sum+=a[i];
            int need = sum - t;
            if (map.containsKey(need)) {
                int index = map.get(need);
                if (index >= prev) {
                    prev = i;
                    count++;
                }
            }
            map.put(sum,i);
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```

