solutions.content:
**Basic Intuition**
* Look Its Likely to have few continous subarray that are not supposed to be intersecting and should match the target value as the total Sum
* A classic defination : subarray sum is just the difference between two prefix sum 
* I get a match if pref[j] - pref[i] = n for j > i , therefore pref[i] = pref[j] - n
* Now this is where Greedy comes into the picture that I get a match of pref[i] for the current pref[j], then lets make this subarray and then say that I cannot use any prefix sum till this j idx (or else further subarrays would intersect with the current one)
* But what if we get continous occurance of same prefix sum, then I am greedily claiming that the last occurance of this prefix sum if always best to have (cuz the length of subarray doesnt matter only count does)
* So the whole problem boils down the storing the last occurances of the prefix sums and each time u get a match and that match is after the last subarray you made lets make this one too and update my last subarray as this one 

**Explaining the implementation**
* Have a unordered Map for storing the last occurance of prefix sums  
* Updating prefix[0] = -1 (empty prefix)
* Have a r variable that would let me know that what is the range I am not supposed to use
* greedy if i get a match for this pos i, update the r, update the ans and move forward
* Anyways, updating the last occurance of the current prefix sum

Happy Coding ^_^

