dp[i] = stores the maximum answer from 0 to i-1 elements.
**transition state : dp[i+1] = max(dp[i+1], dp[j] + 1);**
*if sum from i to j == target.*

Time Complexity = O(N^2).


```
class Solution {
public:
    int maxNonOverlapping(vector<int>& nums, int target) {

    int n = nums.size();
    vector<int> dp(n+1,0);
    for(int i =0; i<n; i++){
        int s= 0;
        for(int j =i; j>=0; j--){
            s+=nums[j];
            dp[i+1] = max(dp[i+1],dp[j]+(s==target?1:0));
        }
    }
    return dp[n];

    }
};
```

