### dynamic programming
We can use prefix sum to find subarrays's sum are equal to ```target```, but only focus on the shortest subarray, we can use these shortest subarray at some positions to construct max number answer.
```dp[i]``` means maximum number of non-empty non-overlapping subarrays's sum == ```target``` in ```nums[0~i-1]```, and return last dp value.
First, we can use prefix sum to find shortest subarray end at cuurent position.
```
dp[0] is 0 because nums[0~-1] is empty. 
dp[i] = max(dp[i-1], dp[preifx[current sum - target]]+1) if current sum - target in preifx else dp[i-1]
```
tc and sc are O(n)
