# Intuition
Try to pick as many subarrays as possible right from the start thats the only way to maximize the count of the sub-arrays picked, that are non-overlapping.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Remember how to get sum of a sub-array via prfix sum difference.



# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int maxNonOverlapping(vector<int>& nums, int target) {

        int n = nums.size();
        vector<int> prfx(n+1, 0);

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            prfx[i+1] = prfx[i] + nums[i];
        }
        int res = 0;
        map<int,bool> mp;mp[0] = true;
        for(int i = 1;i<=n;i++){
            int now = prfx[i];
            int req = prfx[i] - target;

            if(mp.find(req)!=mp.end()){
                res ++;
                mp.clear();
                mp[now] = true;
                continue;
            }
            mp[now] = true;
        }

        return res;
    }
};
```

