# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The intuition behind the problem is to consider all possible subranges between the cutting positions and calculate the cost of cutting each subrange separately. The final cost is the sum of costs for all subranges.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- Sort the cutting positions in ascending order using std::sort to ensure they are in the correct order.
- Initialize a 2D dp (dynamic programming) table with dimensions (m+2) x (m+2), where m is the number of cutting positions.
- Iterate over the length of subranges (s) from 2 to m+1.
- Within each subrange length, iterate over all possible starting positions (i) from 0 to m+1-s.
- Calculate the ending position (j) based on the starting position and subrange length.
- Initialize the cost for the current subrange (dp[i][j]) as infinity (INT_MAX) to track the minimum cost.
- Iterate over all possible cutting positions within the subrange, from i+1 to j-1.
- Calculate the cost of cutting at position k and update the minimum cost for the subrange: dp[i][j] = std::min(dp[i][j], dp[i][k] + dp[k][j]).
- Calculate the cost of cutting the current subrange from the leftmost position (left) to the rightmost position (right).
- The leftmost position (left) is 0 if i is 0, otherwise it is the cutting position at index i-1.
- The rightmost position (right) is n (rod length) if j is m+1, otherwise it is the cutting position at index j-1.
- Add the cost of this subrange to dp[i][j]: dp[i][j] += right - left.
- Repeat steps 3-8 for all subranges of increasing lengths and starting positions.
- The minimum cost of cutting the entire rod is stored in dp[0][m+1], which represents the cost of the subrange from the leftmost position to the rightmost position.
- Return the minimum cost as the result.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N^3)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(N^2)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minCost(int n, std::vector<int>& cuts) {
        std::sort(cuts.begin(), cuts.end());
        int m = cuts.size();
        std::vector<std::vector<int>> dp(m + 2, std::vector<int>(m + 2, 0));

        for (int s = 2; s <= m + 1; s++) {
            for (int i = 0; i + s <= m + 1; i++) {
                int j = i + s;
                dp[i][j] = INT_MAX;
                for (int k = i + 1; k < j; k++) 
                    dp[i][j] = std::min(dp[i][j], dp[i][k] + dp[k][j]);
                int left, right;
                left = (i == 0) ? 0 : cuts[i - 1];
                right = (j == m + 1) ? n : cuts[j - 1];
                dp[i][j] += right - left;
            }
        }
        return dp[0][m + 1];
    }
};
```

