solutions.content:
Here we are breaking a larger stick into smaller sticks at cut_indexes (cut[i]).
**Example:** 0-1-2-3-4-5-6-7 , cuts=[1,3,4,5]
Atlast after breaking at cut_indexes, stick will be like
0-1  1-2-3  3-4  4-5  5-6-7
This result can be acheived in many ways, but we need minimum cost. [cost to cut a stick of length 'L' at any index = L units].
So, we can start to cut from i=0 to 3 at any index and proced further.
Applying recursion with parameters -
start,end..to find cost of a cut,  cut_start,cut_end to know range of  available cuts.
(I) dfs(0,7,0,3)-
	res=7-0=7, irrespective of any cut cost will be its length
	cut_index=0 to 3
	if cut_index=0, cost=left-sub_part=dfs(0,1,0,-1)+right-sub_part=dfs(1,7,1,3)
    if cut_index=1, cost=left-sub_part=dfs(0,3,0,0) + right-sub_part=dfs(3,7,2,3)
	if cut_index=2,cost= left-sub_part=dfs(0,4,0,1) + right-sub_part=dfs(4,7,3,3)
	if cut_index=3, cost=left-sub_part=dfs(0,5,0,2) +right-sub_part=dfs(5,7,4,3).
In this further recursions will be applied for all till the sub-problem becomes small until it can be directly solved (i.e.., base condition=if start> end ).
So we will store the minimum cost at all cut_index , add it our result and return.
There will be many repeated recursion calls, so store caluculated result in hashmap.

**Recursion+memoization:**
```
class Solution {
    int[] cuts;
    HashMap<String,Integer> memo;
    public int minCost(int n, int[] cut_index) {
        memo=new HashMap();
        Arrays.sort(cut_index);
        cuts=cut_index;
        return recur(0,n,0,cuts.length-1);
    }
    private int recur(int start,int end,int cut_start,int cut_end){
        if( cut_start>cut_end ) return 0;
        String key=start+" "+end+" "+cut_start+" "+cut_end;
        if(memo.containsKey(key)) return memo.get(key);
        int res=end-start;
        int val=Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for(int i=cut_start;i<=cut_end;i++)
            val=Math.min(val,recur(start,cuts[i],cut_start,i-1)+recur(cuts[i],end,i+1,cut_end));

        res+=val;
        memo.put(key,res);
        return res;
    }
}
```

**DP approach**:

In DP we pre-caluculate results for smaller sub-problem, and then solve larger problems using these. Here we go backwards.
From 0-1  1-2-3  3-4  4-5  5-6-7 to 0-1-2-3-4-5-6-7.
Here 0-1,1-2-3,3-4 ,4-5,5-6-7 are smallest subproblems as they cannot be furthere divided.We will consider them as stick of **size =1**
We will use a 2D matrix of size (2+number of cuts)(2+number of cuts).
**(I)** cost for breaking stick of **size =2**,
		0-1 1-2-3= 3-0 + cost for 0-1 +cost for 1-3=3+0+0=3.
		1-2-3  3-4 =4-1 + cost for 1-2-3 +cost for 3-4  =3+0+0=3.
		3-4   4-5 =5-3 +cost for 3-4 +cost for 4-5 =2+0+0=2
		4-5  5-6-7=7-4 + cost for 4-5 +cost for 5-6-7 = 3+0+0=3.
**(II)** cost for breaking stick of **size =3**,
      0-1  1-2-3  3-4 =4-0 + min( 0-1+1-4  , 0-3+3-4)=4+min(0+3,3+0) =4+3=7.
	  1-2-3  3-4  4-5 =5-1 + min(1-3 + 3-5 , 1-4 +4-5) =4+min(0+2,3+0) =4+2=6
	   3-4  4-5  5-6-7 =7-3+min( 3-4+4-7 , 3-5+5-7)=4+min(0+3,2+0)=4+2=6.
**(III)** cost for breaking stick of **size =4**,
      0-1  1-2-3  3-4  4-5 = 5-0+ min(0-1+1-5,0-3+3-5,0-4+4-5) = 5+min(0+6,3+2,7+0)=5+5=10.
	  1-2-3  3-4  4-5  5-6-7=7-1+min(1-3+3-7,1-4+4-7,1-5+5-7)=6+(0+6,3+3,6+0)=6+6=12.
**(IV)** cost for breaking stick of **size =5**,
0-1 1-2-3  3-4  4-5 5-6-7 =7-0+min(0-1+1-7,0-3+3-7,0-4+4-7,0-5+5-7)=7+min(0+12,3+6,7+3,10+0)
 .=7+min(12,9,10,10)=7+9=16.
 This works exactly opposite to recursion, in recusrion we break larger problem into smaller. In DP we find results for smaller problems fisrt and then caluculate solution for larger problem.
```
class Solution { 
    public int minCost(int n, int[] cut){
        //Add 0 and n to cut
        int[][] memo=new int[2+cut.length][2+cut.length];

        Arrays.sort(cut);
        int[] cuts = new int[cut.length + 2];
        System.arraycopy(cut, 0, cuts, 1, cut.length);
        cuts[cuts.length-1] = n;

        //Wood of size 1 cannot be cut
        for(int len=2;len<cuts.length;len++){
            for(int row=0;row+len<cuts.length;row++){
                int col=row+len; 
                int val=Integer.MAX_VALUE;
                for(int k=row+1;k<col;k++) 
                    val=Math.min(val,memo[row][k]+memo[k][col]);
                memo[row][col]=cuts[col]-cuts[row]+val;
            }
        }
        return memo[0][memo[0].length-1];
    }
}
```

