# About the problem:
Given a wooden stick of length n units. The stick is labelled from 0 to n. For example, a stick of length 6 is labelled as follows:


Given an integer array cuts where cuts[i] denotes a position you should perform a cut at.

You should perform the cuts in order, you can change the order of the cuts as you wish.

The cost of one cut is the length of the stick to be cut, the total cost is the sum of costs of all cuts. When you cut a stick, it will be split into two smaller sticks (i.e. the sum of their lengths is the length of the stick before the cut). Please refer to the first example for a better explanation.

Return the minimum total cost of the cuts.

# Approach
- Concept used - Bottom up tabulation using dp
- Step by step explaination of the code is done via commented part of code.

# Code
```
/**
 * @param {number} n
 * @param {number[]} cuts
 * @return {number}
 */

//concept used - bottom up tabulation using dp
var minCost = function(n, cuts) {
    cuts.sort((a, b) => a - b) //this sorts the given array from start to end
    cuts = [0, ...cuts, n]//represents the position at which the cut needs to be made between 0 to n
    const stickLen = cuts.length //stick's length is assigned as the length of the cuts arr
    const dp = Array(stickLen).fill(0).map(() => Array(stickLen).fill(0))//base case is defined
    for (let i = stickLen - 2; i >= 0; i--){
        for (let j = i + 2; j < stickLen; j++){
            let minCost = Infinity;
            for (let k = i + 1; k < j; k++){
                //recurrence relation
                const cost = cuts[j] - cuts[i] + dp[i][k] + dp[k][j]
                //cuts[j] - cuts[i] represent length of stick being cut at that position
                //dp[i][k] represents the minimum cost of cutting the stick between positions cuts[i] and cuts[k]
                //dp[k][j] represents the minimum cost of cutting the stick between positions cuts[k] and cuts[j]
