# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
Check the base case: if i > j, return 0 since there are no segments to cut.
Check if the result for the current subproblem is already computed and stored in dp. If so, return the precomputed result.
Initialize mini variable to store the minimum cost for the current subproblem. Set it to a maximum value.
Iterate from i to j to try all possible cut positions within the current subproblem.

For each cut position k, calculate the cost of making the cut at position k. The cost is equal to the length of the segment being cut (cuts[j + 1] - cuts[i - 1]) plus the cost of cutting the left segment recursively (solve(i, k - 1, cuts, dp)) and the cost of cutting the right segment recursively (solve(k + 1, j, cuts, dp)).

Update mini with the minimum cost calculated in the previous step.
Store the minimum cost mini in the dp array for the current subproblem.
Return the minimum cost.

The minCost function initializes the list of cut positions cuts by adding 0 at the beginning and n at the end, representing the start and end positions of the stick. It then sorts the cuts array.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
 O(c^3), where c is the number of cuts.

- Space complexity:
 O(c^2), where c is the number of cuts.
# Code
```
