solutions.content:
**Approach** : MCM : Matrix Chain Multiplication : Because at every index we can make a partition over there.

**Similar Question:** <a href="https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-cost-to-merge-stones/discuss/2332155/easy-mcm-variation-rec-memo-tabulation-comments">1000. Minimum cost to merge stones</a>

**Question Breakdown and thought process:**

Here we are given n sticks and we are given partitition areas where we can make partition. At every partition the cost is the length on which partition is occuring...

**Crux** : The minimum length is 0 and maximum length is n. [0, elements, n]
We will sort the cuts array first and then... we will do insertion.
So, we will insert minimum at first and maximum at last in cuts vector.

Then we can make partition after 1st index to second_last index. as first and last are the heights....

Let's talk about some base cases:
```
1. if(i > j) return 0;  // if we are at invalid index  
```
In the start as we sort the array, so our all cuts are independent of each other...
Valid Range: Here i is at 1st index and j is at second last index.
```
    i        j   
{0, 1, 3, 4, 5, 7}
```
After 1st partition cost : will be arr[j + 1] - arr[i - 1] = 7 - 0 = 7 : which is true.

if we make cut at 3 length stick, then 4, 5, 1 aren't affected from it, they all are independent because of sorting....
```
   ij    i  j 
0 {1} 3 {4, 5} 7
```
if we make cut at 5 length stick, then cost will be = arr[j + 1] - arr[i - 1] = 7 - 3 = 4;
```
   ij   ij
0 {1} 3 {4} 5 7
```
if we make cut at 1 length stick, then cost will be = arr[j + 1] - arr[i - 1] = 3 - 0 = 3;
```
      ij  
0 1 3 {4} 5 7
```
if we make cut at 4 length stick, then cost will be = arr[j + 1] - arr[i - 1] = 5 - 3 = 2;

Total cost = 7 + 4 + 3 + 2 = 16 : which is minimum cost we can obtain from this array.

**Base Case:** Index out of range.
So, if(i > j) return 0;

**Driver Function  :**
as we know : valid partition range from 1st to second last_index : that's why we call rec : 
rec(1, cuts.size()-2);

In Induction Step : 
we have to run for loop from i to j.. : including j : as cuts.size()-2 is last_valid_partition...

for(int k = i; k <= j; k++){

}

For every call : Cost : will be cost[j+1] - cost[i-1];

If we make cut at kth index : then we need to get sum of rec(i, k-1) + rec(k+1, j) + cost;

and in the end we get minimum one...
**Recursion:**
```
// TC: O(N*(2^N))
// SC: O(N*(2^N)) + O(N) auxilary space
class Solution {
public:
    int rec(int i, int j, vector<int> &cuts){
        if(i > j) return 0;

        int mini = INT_MAX;
        for(int k = i; k <= j; k++){
            int cost = rec(i, k-1, cuts) + rec(k+1, j, cuts) + (cuts[j+1] - cuts[i-1]);
            mini = min(mini, cost);
        }
        return mini;
    }
    int minCost(int n, vector<int>& cuts){
        // cuts.insert(cuts.begin(), 0); // here we can insert 0 by emplace_back : as they are going to be sorted...
        cuts.emplace_back(0);
        cuts.emplace_back(n);

        sort(cuts.begin(), cuts.end());

        return rec(1, cuts.size()-2, cuts);
    }
};
```
**Memoization:**
```
// TC: O(N*N*N) = O(N^3)
// SC: O(N^2) + O(N) Auxilary Stack Space
class Solution {
public:
    int memo[101][101];
    int rec(int i, int j, vector<int> &cuts){
        if(i > j) return 0;
        if(memo[i][j] != -1) return memo[i][j];
        int mini = INT_MAX;
        for(int k = i; k <= j; k++){
            int cost = rec(i, k-1, cuts) + rec(k+1, j, cuts) + (cuts[j+1] - cuts[i-1]);
            mini = min(mini, cost);
        }
        return memo[i][j] = mini;
    }
    int minCost(int n, vector<int>& cuts) {
        sort(cuts.begin(), cuts.end());

        cuts.emplace_back(n);
        cuts.insert(cuts.begin(), 0);

        memset(memo, -1, sizeof(memo));
        return rec(1, cuts.size()-2, cuts);
    }
};
```
**Memoization to Tabulation :**
```
Top Down --> Bottom Up :
1. Fill the base cases.
2. Convert : rec(i, j) -> dp[i][j];
3. Set valid ranges in for loop.
4. Copy recurrence from Recursion : )
```

In Memo Base Call : rec(1, cuts.size()-2, memo);

Means we will get our answer at dp[1][cuts.size()-2];

Also, in recursion for i : we will go like 1st to second_last_index..

So, in bottom up we will go like second_last_index to 1.
for(int i = cuts.size()-2; i > 0; i--){

}

Also, in recurison our dp[1][cuts.size()-2] : means for jth index we get ans in second last_index : means we have to fill the 1 to second_last_index : to get answer..

So, our dp second loop will go from 1 to second_last_index:

Catch : Our valid index range is of (i < j) and if(i > j) occur it's invalid and answer is 0;

So, our j loop will start from ith index to Second_last_index instead of 1...

for(int j = i; j < cuts.size()-1; i++)

and we will store minimum answer and then return it..
```
// TC: O(N^3) & SC: O(N^2)
class Solution {
public:
    int minCost(int n, vector<int>& cuts) {
        // cuts.insert(cuts.begin(), 0); // here we can insert 0 by emplace_back : as they are going to be sorted...
        cuts.emplace_back(0);
        cuts.emplace_back(n);

        sort(cuts.begin(), cuts.end());

        // vector<vector<int>> dp (cuts.size(), vector<int> (cuts.size(), 0));
        n = cuts.size();

        int dp[n][n];

        // Filling the first base case : if(i > j) return 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            for(int j = 0; j < i; j++) dp[i][j] = 0;
        }

        // Filling the rest...
        for(int i = cuts.size()-2; i > 0; i--){
            for(int j = i; j < cuts.size()-1; j++){
                int mini = INT_MAX;

                for(int k = i; k <= j; k++){
                    int cost = dp[i][k-1] + dp[k+1][j] + (cuts[j+1] - cuts[i-1]);
                    mini = min(mini, cost);
                }
                dp[i][j] = mini;
            }
        }

        return dp[1][cuts.size()-2];
    }
};
/*
Nested loop condition : )
    either we can start loop at j = i to cut.size() - 2
    or 
    we can start j = 0; and then we can add if else to handle out of range...
    if(i > j){
        dp[i][j] = 0;
        continue;
    }
*/
```
